"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\" />\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"noindex, nofollow\" />\n<title>The AI & Automation Stack Playbook — StackPilot</title>\n<link rel=\"preconnect\" href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com\" />\n<link rel=\"preconnect\" href=\"https://fonts.gstatic.com\" crossorigin />\n<link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800&display=swap\" rel=\"stylesheet\" />\n<script src=\"https://cdn.tailwindcss.com\"></script>\n<script>\ntailwind.config = {\n  theme: {\n    extend: {\n      fontFamily: { sans: ['Inter', 'system-ui', 'sans-serif'] },\n      colors: {\n        brand: { DEFAULT: '#4f46e5', dark: '#3730a3', light: '#818cf8' },\n        surface: '#f8fafc',\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n</script>\n<style>\n  body { font-family: 'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif; }\n  table { border-collapse: collapse; }\n  .pb-section h2 { scroll-margin-top: 5rem; }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body class=\"bg-white text-slate-800\">\n\n<!-- ── HEADER ────────────────────────────────────────────── -->\n<header class=\"border-b border-slate-100 sticky top-0 z-50 bg-white/95 backdrop-blur-sm\">\n<div class=\"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 h-14 flex items-center justify-between\">\n<a href=\"/\" class=\"flex items-center gap-2 font-bold text-xl text-brand\">\n<span class=\"text-2xl\">🧭</span> StackPilot\n</a>\n<span class=\"text-xs font-semibold text-green-700 bg-green-50 px-3 py-1 rounded-full\">✓ Purchase confirmed</span>\n</div>\n</header>\n\n<!-- ── HERO ──────────────────────────────────────────────── -->\n<section class=\"bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-900 via-slate-800 to-brand py-14 px-4 text-white\">\n<div class=\"max-w-4xl mx-auto\">\n<div class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-white/10 border border-white/20 rounded-full px-4 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium mb-6\">\nUpdated June 2026\n</div>\n<h1 class=\"text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold leading-tight mb-4\">The AI & Automation Stack Playbook</h1>\n<p class=\"text-lg text-slate-300 max-w-2xl\">\nThanks for picking this up. Bookmark this page — it's yours for good, and we'll fold in re-tested pricing and picks each quarter. Below: tool picks by use case, side-by-side pricing, a 30-day setup order, and the questions that get vendors to stop steering you.\n</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n\n<!-- ── TABLE OF CONTENTS ─────────────────────────────────── -->\n<section class=\"py-8 px-4 border-b border-slate-100 bg-surface\">\n<div class=\"max-w-4xl mx-auto\">\n<div class=\"text-xs font-semibold text-brand uppercase tracking-wide mb-3\">In this guide</div>\n<div class=\"grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-x-8 gap-y-2 text-sm\">\n<a href=\"#how-to-use\" class=\"text-slate-600 hover:text-brand\">1. How to use this guide</a>\n<a href=\"#crm\" class=\"text-slate-600 hover:text-brand\">2. CRM & pipeline</a>\n<a href=\"#automation\" class=\"text-slate-600 hover:text-brand\">3. Automation / workflow</a>\n<a href=\"#projects\" class=\"text-slate-600 hover:text-brand\">4. Project & work management</a>\n<a href=\"#seo\" class=\"text-slate-600 hover:text-brand\">5. SEO & content research</a>\n<a href=\"#outbound\" class=\"text-slate-600 hover:text-brand\">6. Outbound & sales intelligence</a>\n<a href=\"#writing\" class=\"text-slate-600 hover:text-brand\">7. AI writing & docs</a>\n<a href=\"#setup-order\" class=\"text-slate-600 hover:text-brand\">8. The 30-day setup order</a>\n<a href=\"#demo-questions\" class=\"text-slate-600 hover:text-brand\">9. Questions before any demo call</a>\n<a href=\"#stacking\" class=\"text-slate-600 hover:text-brand\">10. Common stacking mistakes</a>\n</div>\n</div>\n</section>\n\n<div class=\"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-14 space-y-16 pb-section\">\n\n<!-- ── HOW TO USE ────────────────────────────────────────── -->\n<section id=\"how-to-use\">\n<h2 class=\"text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4\">1. How to use this guide</h2>\n<p class=\"text-slate-600 mb-3\">This isn't a \"best 10 tools\" ranking. It's organized the way you actually buy software: by the job you're trying to get done. Pick your use case, read the honest tradeoffs, check the pricing table for your size, then follow the 30-day order so you're not paying for five overlapping subscriptions in month one.</p>\n<p class=\"text-slate-600\">A rule of thumb before you buy anything: if you can't describe the specific workflow the tool replaces in one sentence, you're not ready to buy it yet — you're shopping to feel productive. Write the sentence first.</p>\n</section>\n\n<!-- ── CRM ───────────────────────────────────────────────── -->\n<section id=\"crm\">\n<h2 class=\"text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2\">2. CRM & pipeline</h2>\n<p class=\"text-slate-600 mb-6\">Get this wrong and every other tool in your stack becomes harder to justify, because your source of truth on customers is inconsistent.</p>\n\n<div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-6 mb-6\">\n<h3 class=\"font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2\">Our pick: HubSpot</h3>\n<p class=\"text-sm text-slate-600 mb-3\">The free tier is genuinely usable past the first 5 customers, which almost no competitor can say. You outgrow it on marketing automation and reporting depth before you outgrow it on core CRM. Start free, upgrade only the specific hub (Marketing, Sales, Service) that's actually constraining you — don't buy the bundle up front.</p>\n<p class=\"text-sm text-slate-500\"><strong>Watch out for:</strong> per-seat pricing on paid tiers climbs fast once you're past 3-5 users. Model your cost at 2x your current headcount before committing annually.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-6 mb-6\">\n<h3 class=\"font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2\">Alternatives worth knowing</h3>\n<ul class=\"text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-2\">\n<li><strong>Pipedrive</strong> — simpler, cheaper, built for solo/small sales teams who want pipeline visibility without marketing bloat.</li>\n<li><strong>Monday CRM</strong> — good if you're already on Monday.com for project work and want one system instead of two.</li>\n<li><strong>Airtable + a form</strong> — legitimate option under 3 people. Don't buy a CRM before you have a repeatable sales process to put in it.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<table class=\"w-full text-sm mb-2\">\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"border-b border-slate-200 text-left text-slate-500\">\n<th class=\"py-2 pr-4\">Tool</th><th class=\"py-2 pr-4\">Free tier</th><th class=\"py-2 pr-4\">Entry paid tier</th><th class=\"py-2\">Best for</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody class=\"text-slate-700\">\n<tr class=\"border-b border-slate-100\"><td class=\"py-2 pr-4\">HubSpot</td><td class=\"py-2 pr-4\">Yes, unlimited users</td><td class=\"py-2 pr-4\">~$15-20/seat/mo</td><td class=\"py-2\">Growing teams, marketing + sales together</td></tr>\n<tr class=\"border-b border-slate-100\"><td class=\"py-2 pr-4\">Pipedrive</td><td class=\"py-2 pr-4\">No (14-day trial)</td><td class=\"py-2 pr-4\">~$12-15/seat/mo</td><td class=\"py-2\">Simple sales pipeline, small teams</td></tr>\n<tr><td class=\"py-2 pr-4\">Monday CRM</td><td class=\"py-2 pr-4\">No</td><td class=\"py-2 pr-4\">~$12/seat/mo</td><td class=\"py-2\">Teams already on Monday.com</td></tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p class=\"text-xs text-slate-400\">Pricing shifts — treat these as ballpark for budgeting, confirm current numbers before you buy.</p>\n</section>\n\n<!-- ── AUTOMATION ────────────────────────────────────────── -->\n<section id=\"automation\">\n<h2 class=\"text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2\">3. Automation / workflow</h2>\n<p class=\"text-slate-600 mb-6\">This is the category with the biggest gap between marketing pricing and real cost at scale.</p>\n\n<div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-6 mb-6\">\n<h3 class=\"font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2\">Our pick: Make</h3>\n<p class=\"text-sm text-slate-600 mb-3\">Visual, more powerful branching logic than Zapier, and meaningfully cheaper once you're past a few thousand operations a month. The tradeoff is a steeper first-week learning curve — budget a real afternoon to learn the scenario builder, not 20 minutes.</p>\n<p class=\"text-sm text-slate-500\"><strong>Watch out for:</strong> \"operations\" pricing punishes chatty workflows (one row of data touching five modules burns five ops). Design scenarios to batch where you can.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-6 mb-6\">\n<h3 class=\"font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2\">When Zapier is actually the right call</h3>\n<p class=\"text-sm text-slate-600\">If your team isn't technical and you need something a non-builder can maintain after you leave, Zapier's simpler linear model is worth the pricing premium. Don't choose Make just because it's cheaper if nobody on the team will actually maintain the scenarios.</p>\n</div>\n\n<table class=\"w-full text-sm mb-2\">\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"border-b border-slate-200 text-left text-slate-500\">\n<th class=\"py-2 pr-4\">Tool</th><th class=\"py-2 pr-4\">Free tier</th><th class=\"py-2 pr-4\">Entry paid tier</th><th class=\"py-2\">Best for</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody class=\"text-slate-700\">\n<tr class=\"border-b border-slate-100\"><td class=\"py-2 pr-4\">Make</td><td class=\"py-2 pr-4\">1,000 ops/mo</td><td class=\"py-2 pr-4\">~$9-16/mo</td><td class=\"py-2\">Cost-sensitive, complex branching logic</td></tr>\n<tr><td class=\"py-2 pr-4\">Zapier</td><td class=\"py-2 pr-4\">100 tasks/mo</td><td class=\"py-2 pr-4\">~$20-30/mo</td><td class=\"py-2\">Non-technical teams, simplest possible setup</td></tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</section>\n\n<!-- ── PROJECTS ──────────────────────────────────────────── -->\n<section id=\"projects\">\n<h2 class=\"text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2\">4. Project & work management</h2>\n<p class=\"text-slate-600 mb-6\">The category where the tool matters less than whether your team actually agrees to use one system.</p>\n\n<div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-6 mb-6\">\n<h3 class=\"font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2\">Our pick: ClickUp (free tier) or Monday.com (paid)</h3>\n<p class=\"text-sm text-slate-600 mb-3\">ClickUp's free forever plan is the most generous in the category — tasks, docs, and light automation without a card on file. Monday.com costs more but the UI is easier for non-technical teams to adopt without training, which matters more than feature count if adoption is your real risk.</p>\n</div>\n\n<table class=\"w-full text-sm mb-2\">\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"border-b border-slate-200 text-left text-slate-500\">\n<th class=\"py-2 pr-4\">Tool</th><th class=\"py-2 pr-4\">Free tier</th><th class=\"py-2 pr-4\">Entry paid tier</th><th class=\"py-2\">Best for</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody class=\"text-slate-700\">\n<tr class=\"border-b border-slate-100\"><td class=\"py-2 pr-4\">ClickUp</td><td class=\"py-2 pr-4\">Yes, generous</td><td class=\"py-2 pr-4\">~$7/seat/mo</td><td class=\"py-2\">Budget-conscious, tech-comfortable teams</td></tr>\n<tr><td class=\"py-2 pr-4\">Monday.com</td><td class=\"py-2 pr-4\">No (14-day trial)</td><td class=\"py-2 pr-4\">~$12/seat/mo</td><td class=\"py-2\">Easiest adoption, cross-functional teams</td></tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</section>\n\n<!-- ── SEO ───────────────────────────────────────────────── -->\n<section id=\"seo\">\n<h2 class=\"text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2\">5. SEO & content research</h2>\n<p class=\"text-slate-600 mb-6\">The one category here where the tool genuinely can pay for itself in a measurable way — if you actually publish consistently.</p>\n\n<div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-6 mb-6\">\n<h3 class=\"font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2\">Our pick: Semrush</h3>\n<p class=\"text-sm text-slate-600 mb-3\">Keyword research, competitor gap analysis, and site audits in one subscription instead of three. The 7-day trial is enough to run one real competitor audit — do that before the trial ends rather than poking around aimlessly.</p>\n<p class=\"text-sm text-slate-500\"><strong>Don't buy this</strong> if you're not committing to a monthly publishing cadence. The tool doesn't write content for you; it tells you what to write, and it's wasted spend if nothing gets published on the back of it.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-6 mb-6\">\n<h3 class=\"font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2\">Cheaper alternative: Surfer SEO</h3>\n<p class=\"text-sm text-slate-600\">Narrower tool — on-page content optimization only, no full site audit or backlink data. Worth it if you already know your keywords and just need help structuring individual articles to rank.</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n\n<!-- ── OUTBOUND ──────────────────────────────────────────── -->\n<section id=\"outbound\">\n<h2 class=\"text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2\">6. Outbound & sales intelligence</h2>\n<p class=\"text-slate-600 mb-6\">Contact data quality varies more than any other category here — test before you commit to an annual plan.</p>\n\n<div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-6 mb-6\">\n<h3 class=\"font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2\">Our pick: Apollo.io</h3>\n<p class=\"text-sm text-slate-600 mb-3\">Large contact database, built-in sequencing, and a genuinely usable free tier for testing data quality on your specific target accounts before you pay. Run a real search against 20 known-good target companies before upgrading — that tells you more than any review.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-6 mb-6\">\n<h3 class=\"font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2\">If you need higher data accuracy: Clay</h3>\n<p class=\"text-sm text-slate-600\">More expensive and more complex to set up (it's a workflow builder on top of dozens of data sources), but the enrichment quality and waterfall lookups beat single-source tools when accuracy matters more than speed.</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n\n<!-- ── WRITING ───────────────────────────────────────────── -->\n<section id=\"writing\">\n<h2 class=\"text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2\">7. AI writing & docs</h2>\n<p class=\"text-slate-600 mb-6\">The category most likely to already be covered by something you pay for. Check before buying a dedicated tool.</p>\n<div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-6\">\n<p class=\"text-sm text-slate-600 mb-2\">Notion AI (if you're already paying for Notion), the AI features built into your existing CRM, or a general assistant subscription usually covers 80% of small-business writing needs — first drafts, meeting summaries, email cleanup. Reach for a specialized tool only when you have a specific, recurring, high-volume writing task a general assistant handles poorly (e.g., structured SEO content at scale, which routes back to the SEO section above).</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n\n<!-- ── SETUP ORDER ───────────────────────────────────────── -->\n<section id=\"setup-order\">\n<h2 class=\"text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4\">8. The 30-day setup order</h2>\n<p class=\"text-slate-600 mb-6\">The single biggest mistake we see: turning on 4 tools in week one, none of them properly configured, all of them billing you before you know if any of them stick. Do it in this order instead.</p>\n\n<div class=\"space-y-4\">\n<div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-5\">\n<div class=\"text-xs font-semibold text-brand uppercase tracking-wide mb-1\">Week 1</div>\n<p class=\"text-sm text-slate-700\"><strong>CRM only.</strong> Get your existing customer/lead data into HubSpot (or your chosen CRM) free tier. Don't automate anything yet. Just get the source of truth clean — nothing else in this stack works if this data is wrong.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-5\">\n<div class=\"text-xs font-semibold text-brand uppercase tracking-wide mb-1\">Week 2</div>\n<p class=\"text-sm text-slate-700\"><strong>Project/work management.</strong> Move your team's actual task tracking into one system. Resist adding automation this week — the goal is habit formation, not sophistication.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-5\">\n<div class=\"text-xs font-semibold text-brand uppercase tracking-wide mb-1\">Week 3</div>\n<p class=\"text-sm text-slate-700\"><strong>One automation, end to end.</strong> Pick the single most annoying manual data-entry task (usually: lead form → CRM → notify sales) and build that one Make/Zapier scenario completely. Don't start a second automation until the first one has run cleanly for a week unattended.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-5\">\n<div class=\"text-xs font-semibold text-brand uppercase tracking-wide mb-1\">Week 4</div>\n<p class=\"text-sm text-slate-700\"><strong>Growth tooling (SEO or outbound, not both).</strong> Only add Semrush or Apollo once the operational core above is running on its own. Adding a growth tool before the operational plumbing works just means more leads flowing into a messy process.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</section>\n\n<!-- ── DEMO QUESTIONS ────────────────────────────────────── -->\n<section id=\"demo-questions\">\n<h2 class=\"text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4\">9. Questions to ask before any demo call</h2>\n<p class=\"text-slate-600 mb-4\">Sales reps steer demos toward their strongest features. These questions redirect back to your actual situation:</p>\n<ul class=\"text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-3 list-disc pl-5\">\n<li>\"What does this cost at <em>2x</em> my current usage/seats — not today's usage?\" (Reveals the real scaling cost, not the intro price.)</li>\n<li>\"What's the most common reason customers our size churn?\" (A rep who can't answer this hasn't sold to your segment.)</li>\n<li>\"Can I export all my data in a usable format if I leave?\" (Tests for lock-in before you're dependent on it.)</li>\n<li>\"What breaks first if my team doubles?\" (Surfaces per-seat traps and hidden tier walls.)</li>\n<li>\"Show me the exact workflow I described, not your best-case demo flow.\" (Forces them off the script.)</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n\n<!-- ── STACKING MISTAKES ─────────────────────────────────── -->\n<section id=\"stacking\">\n<h2 class=\"text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4\">10. Common stacking mistakes</h2>\n<ul class=\"text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-3 list-disc pl-5\">\n<li><strong>Buying the annual plan before the monthly plan proves out.</strong> Annual discounts are real, but a bad monthly bet you can cancel beats a bad annual bet you're locked into.</li>\n<li><strong>Two tools doing the same job \"just in case.\"</strong> If your CRM has basic automation and you also buy Zapier for the same task, pick one and cancel the other after 30 days — don't let both auto-renew \"to be safe.\"</li>\n<li><strong>Automating a broken process.</strong> Automation makes a good process faster and a bad process fail faster. Fix the workflow manually first, then automate it.</li>\n<li><strong>No owner.</strong> Every tool in this stack needs one named person responsible for it, even if it's you. Tools with no owner quietly stop being maintained and keep billing anyway.</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n\n</div>\n\n<!-- ── FOOTER ────────────────────────────────────────────── -->\n<footer class=\"border-t border-slate-100 py-10 px-4 text-center\">\n<p class=\"text-sm text-slate-500 mb-2\">Thanks for supporting independent, ad-free tool reviews.</p>\n<a href=\"/\" class=\"text-sm font-medium text-brand hover:text-brand-dark\">← Back to StackPilot</a>\n</footer>\n\n</body>\n</html>\n"